afterSOLIDrevisionEHL.model

Class CD

  • java.lang.Object
    • afterSOLIDrevisionEHL.model.Element
      • afterSOLIDrevisionEHL.model.SimpleElement
        • afterSOLIDrevisionEHL.model.CD
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Requestable, java.lang.Comparable<Element>

    public class CD
extends SimpleElement
    Class whose instances represent a CD. A CD has a title and a number of tracks. Instances of CD are ordered in descending order of number of tracks.
    Author:
    (original) Daniel Gomes, Filipe Maia, Pedro Antunes, (revisionSOLID) Eva Gomes, Hugo Leal, Lucas Andrade

    • Method Detail

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(Element cd)
        Sorts instances of CD by descending order of number of tracks; if two instances of CD have the same number of tracks, they are lexicologically ordered by their title.

        If cd is not an instance of CD, it is returned the result of the compareTo of class Element.

        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<Element>
        Overrides:
        compareTo in class Element
        Parameters:
        cd - The instance of Element with which to compare to.
        Returns:
        A value less than 0 if this is less than element; 0 if this and element have the same title and the same runtime type or a value greater than 0 if this is greater than element.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If element is null.
